This is the entrance to Piopiotahi (Milford Sound) from the Tasman Sea. I was standing at the front of a small cruise boat when I captured this shot earlier this month. The wind gusts were sweeping off the peaks and hitting the boat at 110kmph. I loved the drama of the moment, but ending up in the Tasman would have been an interesting story.
